article.headline: Ware runs for 205 yards, 3 TDs as USC beats Oregon St. 38-21
article.description: Aca'Cedric Ware rushed for 205 yards and three touchdowns, including 57-yard and 62-yard scoring sprints, as Southern California beat Oregon State 38-21 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Ware runs for 205 yards, 3 TDs as USC beats Oregon St. 38-21

images.name: Ware goes 62 yards for 3rd rush TD of night
images.caption: Aca'Cedric Ware gets into the open field and outruns the defense all the way to the end zone, growing the Trojans' 4th-quarter lead to 35-21.

video.headline: Ware goes 62 yards for 3rd rush TD of night
video.caption: Aca'Cedric Ware gets into the open field and outruns the defense all the way to the end zone, growing the Trojans' 4th-quarter lead to 35-21.
video.title: Ware goes 62 yards for 3rd rush TD of night
video.description: Aca'Cedric Ware gets into the open field and outruns the defense all the way to the end zone, growing the Trojans' 4th-quarter lead to 35-21.

article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Aca'Cedric Ware rushed for 205 yards and three touchdowns, including 57-yard and 62-yard scoring sprints, as Southern California beat Oregon State 38-21 on Saturday night. JT Daniels threw for 177 yards and a touchdown and Vavae Malepeai added 101 yards rushing for the Trojans (5-4, 4-3 Pac-12), who snapped a two-game losing streak. Jake Luton went 31-for-45 for 301 yards and a touchdown and Isaiah Hodgins had 129 yards receiving for the Beavers (2-7, 1-5). Southern California stormed out to a 21-0 lead thanks in part to a grinding 17-play first drive and a lightning strike 57-yarder from Ware on the Trojans' second possession. But Oregon State recovered and trailed 21-14 at the half. The Beavers' second touchdown, an 11-yard catch by Noah Togiai with four seconds before the break, capped an 85-yard drive that lasted just 67 seconds. Southern California opened the second half with a drive that led to a 2-yard Ware touchdown, but Oregon State responded with its own touchdown run by Artavis Pierce. With 11:53 remaining, Ware uncorked his 62-yarder to make the score 35-21. Daniels suffered a concussion two weeks ago versus Utah and returned as the Southern California starter on Saturday. Luton returned as the starter for Oregon State after missing four weeks with an ankle injury. Last week, he came in during the second half against Colorado and passed for 310 yards and three touchdowns and was named the Pac-12 Offensive Player of the Week. THE TAKEAWAY Southern California: Coach Clay Helton took over play calling duties and fired the offensive line coach after last week's loss. The offense looked particularly crisp to open the game and at the start of the second half. . Southern California averaged 7.5 yards per carry against the Beavers defense. . Just one more win makes Southern California bowl eligible. Oregon State: The Trojans looked determined to stuff the run, but with Luton back behind center, the Beavers are a different team. Oregon State's remaining schedule appears brutal, but if Luton can stay healthy, things look somewhat brighter. UP NEXT Southern California hosts California on Nov. 10. Oregon State plays at Stanford on Nov. 10.

videos.headline: USC strikes first with 8-yard TD run
videos.description: Stephen Carr finds an opening and gets to the end zone, giving the Trojans an early 7-0 lead on the Beavers.

videos.headline: Ware doubles USC lead with 57-yard TD run
videos.description: Aca'Cedric Ware slips out of a tackle and takes it all the way to the house, making it 14-0 Trojans early in the 2nd quarter.

videos.headline: Daniels drops dime for 41-yard TD pass
videos.description: JT Daniels lets one rip down the sideline, hitting Devon Williams in stride and extending the Trojans' lead to 21-0.

videos.headline: Colletto narrows lead with 6-yard QB run
videos.description: Jack Colletto fakes the hand-off and keeps it himself, getting to the edge and crossing the goal line to cut the Trojans' lead to 21-7.

videos.headline: Togiai makes twisting grab for 11-yard TD
videos.description: Jake Luton throws it up for TE Noah Togiai, who leaves his feet to make a spectacular leaping catch and trim the Trojans' lead to 21-14.

videos.headline: Ware extends USC lead with 2nd TD of game
videos.description: Aca'Cedric Ware hits a hole and gets to the end zone for a 2-yard touchdown run, making it 28-14 Trojans.

videos.headline: Pierce cuts lead in half with 6-yard TD run
videos.description: RB Artavis Pierce squeezes through an opening and into the end zone to narrow the Trojans' lead to 28-21.

videos.headline: Beavers force crucial 4th-quarter fumble
videos.description: Matthew Tago strips the ball free from Vavae Malepeai, and Jalen Moore recovers to give the ball back to Oregon State after video review.
